00:41:33.260 --> 00:41:34.670
I'm going to let him have it.

00:41:34.670 --> 00:41:36.020
I know this is going
to be disastrous.

00:41:36.020 --> 00:41:37.145
I'm just going to be quiet.

00:41:37.145 --> 00:41:40.300
Because I'm tired of being the
one that's always speaking up.

00:41:40.300 --> 00:41:43.510
And on that day, when the
campaign is checked off

00:41:43.510 --> 00:41:46.330
and it goes out, and people
lose their minds on social,

00:41:46.330 --> 00:41:49.240
because of course, it's
a terrible landing,

00:41:49.240 --> 00:41:51.700
I'm always, like,
there was definitely--

00:41:51.700 --> 00:41:56.740
this is a failure of leadership
beyond just the leader

00:41:56.740 --> 00:41:57.520
not seeing it.

00:41:57.520 --> 00:42:00.940
It means the leader has been
breeding an environment where

00:42:00.940 --> 00:42:02.350
they can't be challenged.

00:42:02.350 --> 00:42:04.210
And that person who
went to speak up

00:42:04.210 --> 00:42:06.990
did not feel like
they had the place.

00:42:06.990 --> 00:42:10.320
I'm telling you, if
you have a company that

00:42:10.320 --> 00:42:14.850
