what would be your advice

00:43:40.650 --> 00:43:43.770
to spot those things
and take action,

00:43:43.770 --> 00:43:47.340
although it's not visible,
or it's not super clear

00:43:47.340 --> 00:43:49.530
what that is?

00:43:49.530 --> 00:43:51.100
LUVVIE AJAYI: Just
talking about it--

00:43:51.100 --> 00:43:53.898
you know, if it's
not super clear

00:43:53.898 --> 00:43:55.440
that this thing is
happening, but you

00:43:55.440 --> 00:43:58.260
feel this under tension,
this undercurrent,

00:43:58.260 --> 00:44:00.300
start having a
conversation about it.

00:44:00.300 --> 00:44:02.702
Just being like, I know--

00:44:02.702 --> 00:44:03.910
I've been feeling this thing.

00:44:03.910 --> 00:44:06.990
I don't if anybody else has
been feeling this thing.

00:44:06.990 --> 00:44:08.800
Am I tripping?

00:44:08.800 --> 00:44:10.770
Am I just thinking
too hard about it?

00:44:10.770 --> 00:44:13.860
Even just, yeah, even
the whole too sensitive--

00:44:13.860 --> 00:44:16.540
just have the conversation.

00:44:16.540 --> 00:44:19.030
Here's how I'm feeling.

00:44:19.030 --> 00:44:24.195
Am I being too
sensitive about it?

00:44:24.195 --> 00:44:26.570
Is there something else that
I should be looking out for?

00:44:26.570 --> 00:44:27.440
What can we do?

00:44:27.440 --> 00:44:31.220
Because I feel this
undercurrent of tension.

00:44:31.220 --> 00:44:33.380
I think in the moments
that we are not sure,

00:44:33.380 --> 00:44:35.840
use your words to
say you're not sure.

00:44:35.840 --> 00:44:38.310
You can even say, I
don't know what to do,

00:44:38.310 --> 00:44:40.030
but I see there's
something wrong here.

00:44:40.030 --> 00:44:43.790
That is actually an action, as
opposed to being quiet, trying

00:44:43.790 --> 00:44:47.570
to figure it out in your
head, and then just not saying

00:44:47.570 --> 00:44:48.080
anything.

00:44:48.080 --> 00:44:52.610
I say your lack of
being sure is OK.

00:44:52.610 --> 00:44:55.130
You don't always
have to be sure.

00:44:55.130 --> 00:44:56.630
But I think you can
talk it through.

00:44:56.630 --> 00:44:58.338
Because somebody else
is probably feeling

00:44:58.338 --> 00:45:00.270
unsure, too, about
the same thing.

00:45:00.270 --> 00:45:02.060
And you can work it through.

00:45:02.060 --> 00:45:03.770
I think transparency is huge.

00:45:03.770 --> 00:45:06.020
Vulnerability is huge.

00:45:06.020 --> 00:45:08.640
In the moments when we don't
know, being able to say,

00:45:08.640 --> 00:45:10.140
I don't know.

00:45:10.140 --> 00:45:14.330
We also live in a society
that wants us to always know.

00:45:14.330 --> 00:45:17.322
Like, everything
is figure outable.

00:45:17.322 --> 00:45:18.530
If you don't know, Google it.

00:45:18.530 --> 00:45:21.280
[LAUGHTER]

00:45:21.280 --> 00:45:23.660
But there are some
things you can't Google.

00:45:23.660 --> 00:45:25.070
You can't Google your feelings.

00:45:25.070 --> 00:45:27.320
You can't Google certain
things that haven't happened.

00:45:27.320 --> 00:45:29.420
You can't Google the
undercurrent, right?

00:45:29.420 --> 00:45:31.942
So be able to say to
somebody, you know what?

00:45:31.942 --> 00:45:33.150
There's this thing happening.

00:45:33.150 --> 00:45:35.640
I'm not sure about it,
but it doesn't feel right.

00:45:35.640 --> 00:45:36.830
It's OK.

00:45:36.830 --> 00:45:38.390
I don't know when--

00:45:38.390 --> 00:45:40.970
I don't know how we're
expected to do business

00:45:40.970 --> 00:45:44.900
properly when one, we're not
expected to make mistakes.

00:45:44.900 --> 00:45:48.320
And then we're also not expected
to admit when we're not sure.

00:45:48.320 --> 00:45:49.570
We're always supposed to know.

00:45:49.570 --> 00:45:50.810
So figure it out!

00:45:50.810 --> 00:45:53.180
No, you didn't know,
say you don't know.

00:45:53.180 --> 00:45:54.670
I think talk it through.

00:45:54.670 --> 00:45:58.070
But again, I think it might even
take spaces like this, right?

00:45:58.070 --> 00:46:00.080
Where maybe once a
month-- and I think

00:46:00.080 --> 00:46:04.230
Google has this program in other
places, but just in general,

00:46:04.230 --> 00:46:06.990
it helps to just have a
space where you can be, like,

00:46:06.990 --> 00:46:08.130
let's just talk freely.

00:46:08.130 --> 00:46:08.670
What's up?

00:46:08.670 --> 00:46:09.553
How are you feeling?

00:46:09.553 --> 00:46:10.470
How's the environment?

00:46:10.470 --> 00:46:12.470
Do you feel empowered
to speak up?

00:46:12.470 --> 00:46:16.080
You know, you may be able to, in
the room with 40 other people,

00:46:16.080 --> 00:46:19.910
be able to say I can't
really put my finger on it.

00:46:19.910 --> 00:46:22.182
But things don't feel right.

00:46:22.182 --> 00:46:23.890
And then other people
can be, like, yeah,

00:46:23.890 --> 00:46:27.480
there's this weird tension that
I started noticing after this.

00:46:27.480 --> 00:46:29.010
Talk it through as a company.

00:46:29.010 --> 00:46:33.020
Talk it through as a
department, as a team.

00:46:33.020 --> 00:46:35.020
But again, it has to
be the environment that

00:46:35.020 --> 00:46:36.280
has fostered that, right?

00:46:36.280 --> 00:46:40.090
So hopefully it
becomes the environment

00:46:40.090 --> 00:46:41.470
that then fosters that.

00:46:41.470 --> 00:46:44.610
I think companies like
Google are at least trying.

00:46:44.610 --> 00:46:46.670
We'll fall short.

00:46:46.670 --> 00:46:47.710
That's to be expected.

00:46:47.710 --> 00:46:51.580
It's not going to be all of a
sudden everybody's kum ba yah.

00:46:51.580 --> 00:46:55.163
But the attempt is
at least necessary.

00:46:55.163 --> 00:46:55.830
AUDIENCE: Great.

