00:51:29.740 --> 00:51:33.960
But the concept is always
punch up, not punch down.

00:51:33.960 --> 00:51:37.220
Which means if you're going to
talk about somebody's identity

00:51:37.220 --> 00:51:39.710
and use it in a
point of a joke, it

00:51:39.710 --> 00:51:41.600
can't be a point
of identity that is

00:51:41.600 --> 00:51:43.190
more marginalized than yours.

00:51:43.190 --> 00:51:45.260
So I can't make fun--

00:51:45.260 --> 00:51:48.290
I'm Christian-- I can't
make a joke about somebody's

00:51:48.290 --> 00:51:49.830
Muslim identity.

00:51:49.830 --> 00:51:50.690
I am straight.

00:51:50.690 --> 00:51:53.720
I can't make a joke about
somebody's gay identity.

00:51:53.720 --> 00:51:54.980
You know what I mean?

00:51:54.980 --> 00:51:56.960
So you have to kind of
operate in that way.

00:51:56.960 --> 00:52:01.860
So a white man who is well off
writing a poem that essentially

00:52:01.860 --> 00:52:04.277
is making fun of somebody who's
homeless is punching down.

00:52:04.277 --> 00:52:04.902
AUDIENCE: Well.

00:52:04.902 --> 00:52:06.112
He wasn't making fun of that.

00:52:06.112 --> 00:52:08.320
That's my-- I mean, obviously,
I didn't [INAUDIBLE]..

00:52:08.320 --> 00:52:09.112
LUVVIE AJAYI: Yeah.

00:52:09.112 --> 00:52:11.240
But essentially think
about it, right?

00:52:11.240 --> 00:52:12.860
We're also in a
moment where we're

00:52:12.860 --> 00:52:16.520
seeing fashion-- for example,
in the US in the last month,

00:52:16.520 --> 00:52:20.780
three major brands
have been in hot fire

00:52:20.780 --> 00:52:24.020
because they created
products that

00:52:24.020 --> 00:52:26.720
look like blackface,
which historically

00:52:26.720 --> 00:52:28.770
has denigrated black people.

00:52:28.770 --> 00:52:30.640
So in that moment, you
can be, like, well,

00:52:30.640 --> 00:52:34.520
it's just this thing with red
lips that happens to be black.

00:52:34.520 --> 00:52:35.740
What if it's just fashion?

00:52:35.740 --> 00:52:37.790
Are we stifling the
creativity now because

00:52:37.790 --> 00:52:39.860
of political correctness?

00:52:39.860 --> 00:52:40.400
No.

00:52:40.400 --> 00:52:43.470
It takes historical
context into effect.

00:52:43.470 --> 00:52:45.410
So I think it's just
an interesting time.

00:52:45.410 --> 00:52:48.050
There's going to be a lot of
mistakes being made, right,

00:52:48.050 --> 00:52:48.860
across the board.

00:52:48.860 --> 00:52:51.540
People are going to
make poor choices.

00:52:51.540 --> 00:52:54.470
But we have to then fix it.

00:52:54.470 --> 00:52:56.780
When we call them
in or call them out,

00:52:56.780 --> 00:52:58.760
the point is that,
the hope is they

00:52:58.760 --> 00:53:00.140
don't make the mistake again.

00:53:00.140 --> 00:53:01.760
They see where the error is.

00:53:01.760 --> 00:53:04.400
And in that moment when
you are challenged,

00:53:04.400 --> 00:53:07.830
you don't instantly go
to I'm being trolled.

00:53:07.830 --> 00:53:08.330
Right?

00:53:08.330 --> 00:53:11.120
You also go to, OK, what
have I done here that I

00:53:11.120 --> 00:53:14.000
can make sure I don't do again?

00:53:14.000 --> 00:53:18.650
And how can I be an
example of what it

00:53:18.650 --> 00:53:23.000
looks like to redeem yourself?

00:53:23.000 --> 00:53:25.250
So it's an interesting time.

00:53:25.250 --> 00:53:30.725
Again, I just talk about
speaking up in these moments.

00:53:30.725 --> 00:53:32.600
I'm somebody who's
considered a truth teller.

00:53:32.600 --> 00:53:34.670
But I also make mistakes, right?

00:53:34.670 --> 00:53:38.120
And my mistakes are
also loud mistakes,

00:53:38.120 --> 00:53:40.800
because I have such
a giant platform.

00:53:40.800 --> 00:53:44.610
So if I'm ever afraid of
making too many mistakes,

00:53:44.610 --> 00:53:48.020
and I make that stop
me from speaking up,

00:53:48.020 --> 00:53:50.750
essentially what am I losing?

00:53:50.750 --> 00:53:55.500
I can't be so afraid of making
mistakes that I shut up.

00:53:55.500 --> 00:53:58.710
I just have to be willing
to make mistakes and then

00:53:58.710 --> 00:54:00.600
grow from them.

00:54:00.600 --> 00:54:03.330
And that is ultimately
what we can all do.

00:54:03.330 --> 00:54:04.860
If you're willing
to make mistakes,

00:54:04.860 --> 00:54:07.030
you're willing to be more risky.

00:54:07.030 --> 00:54:09.510
And then when you make those
mistakes, try to grow from it.

00:54:09.510 --> 00:54:11.718
Try to learn from it and
try to figure out how to not

00:54:11.718 --> 00:54:13.285
make the same mistake again.

